symbols.name: sap.sac.df.FlexAnalysis
symbols.description:
Enables users to view, navigate and change multidimensional data exposed via InA.

Overview

The user can view the data in a Table, navigate in the data via a context menu or builder panels The data source that the FlexAnalysis consumes or renders has to be provided as a property value.

properties.name: title
properties.description: Sets title to be shown in the control. If not set the name of the corresponding back-end query is used

properties.name: showTitle
properties.description: Indicates Flexible Analysis component should display the component title

properties.name: autoUpdate
properties.description: Indicates if Flexible Analysis component automatically requests the ResultSet for the shown data source

properties.name: configurationURI
properties.description: URI of the advanced configuration to be fetched

properties.name: configObject
properties.description: JSON object containing the configuration (alternative to configurationURI)

properties.name: configId
properties.description: configuration Id

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of the component

properties.name: height
properties.description: Height of the component

properties.name: hideDesignPanel
properties.description: Sets if the Design Panel of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: hideStylePanel
properties.description: Sets if the Style Panel of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: hideMenuBar
properties.description: Sets if the menu bar of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: hideStatusBar
properties.description: Sets if the status bar of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: hideToolBar
properties.description: Sets if the toolbar of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: hideFilterLine
properties.description: Sets if the filter of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: hideSideNavigation
properties.description: Sets if the side navigation bar of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: hideLandingPage
properties.description: Sets if the landing page of FlexAnalysis is hidden

properties.name: environment
properties.description: Additional Flag to be passed to the control TODO: Document the possibilities

properties.name: systemName
properties.description: System to take data from. If not set or set to "local" current url will be used to determine the system

properties.name: dataSource
properties.description: Data source (Query name/ View, InA model etc) to be used to get the data from

properties.name: systemType
properties.description: Type the system to connect to get data

properties.name: keepAliveInterval
properties.description: Interval to keep the InA session alive. values less than 1 deactivates the keep alive handling

properties.name: clientIdentifier
properties.description: Client Identifier to be used for underlying InA queries

properties.name: dataProvider
properties.description: Name of the Data Provider from the corresponding MultiDimModel to be used

properties.name: multiDimModelId
properties.description: Id of the MultiDimModel to use

properties.name: implicitVariableHandling
properties.description: Indicates if the variable are handled internal handling by FlexAnalysis. If set to false it is done via corresponding MultiDimModel

properties.name: styleTemplateName
properties.description: Indicates if the variable are handled internal handling by FlexAnalysis. If set to false it is done via corresponding MultiDimModel

symbols.name: sap.sac.df.model.DataProvider
symbols.description:
A data provider is an analytical query exposed via an analytical engine and accessed via InA protocol. It represents a navigable query manager and allows to access and change data. Instances of this class should only be created by the {@link sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel}. Structure of Exposed Data: 

"Name": "",
"DataSourceInfo": { },
"Variables": { }
"Dimensions": { },
"Measures": [ ],
"AxesLayout": {
  "Columns": [],
  "Rows": []
 },
"Grid": { },
"Messages": [ ]

The multidimensional model allows to access and change data accessed via the InA Protocol. The multidimensional model populate it's exposed data in JSON format via binding to controls. Structure of Exposed Data: 

"DataProviders": { },
"VariableGroups": { },
"Messages": [ ]
